\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6560113 IC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3430147\charrsid13393843 
Yes. I mean more like - thirty pence a pint. Thirty pence a pint. Welks was forty. Now - you know where Garner's corner is? It's
 pulled down now. Well right outside Garner, there's a pub there - Ambrose's there was, it was a Limited Company pub. And they used to stand out there with their cockles, jellied eels - very shell fish you can mention, and what happened - they used to sel
l
 out in no time. Then they used to go into Rose's and have a glass of beer, say for a penny, packet of five cigarettes for a penny. And they've had a good night out. I mean to say, the butchers shops up there, they used to sell the meat - next to nothing 
